    • Field Detail

      • coloring

        @Option
public ContoursOptions.ColoringEnum coloring
        Determines the coloring method showing the contour values. Defaults to FILL.

      • end

        @Option
public Integer end
        The ending contour level value. Must be more than "start".

      • labelfont

        @Option
public final FontOptions labelfont
        The font used for labeling the contour levels. The default color comes from the lines, if shown. The default family and size come from "layout.font".

      • labelformat

        @Option
public String labelformat
        The contour label formatting rule using d3 formatting mini-language which is very similar to Python, see d3 formatting reference.

      • operation

        @Option
public ContoursOptions.ConstraintOperationEnum operation
        The constraint operation. Open vs closed intervals make no difference to constraint display, but all versions are allowed for consistency with filter transforms.

        Default: EQ

      • showlabels

        @Option
public Boolean showlabels
        Determines whether to label the contour lines with their values.

      • showlines

        @Option
public Boolean showlines
        Determines whether or not the contour lines are drawn. Has an effect only if "coloring" is set to FILL.

      • size

        @Option
public Integer size
        The step between each contour level.

        Constraints: >0

      • start

        @Option
public Integer start
        The starting contour level value.

        Constraints: Must be less than "end"

      • type

        @Option
public ContoursOptions.TypeEnum type
        Controls how data are represented within a contour plot.

      • value$array

        @Option(value="value")
public double[] value$array
        The values of the constraint range as a an array of two numbers where the first is the lower bound and the second is the upper bound. This form requires that "operation" be set to one of the interval values.

      • value$number

        @Option(value="value")
public Double value$number
        The value of the constraint boundary. This form requires that "operation" be set to one of the comparison values.

      • value$string

        @Option(value="value")
public String value$string
        Alternate form where value is a categorical coordinate string.
